Package: censuschat
Title: Chat with U.S. Census Data Using Natural Language
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Sharon", "Machlis", email = "smachlis@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Claude (Anthropic)", role = "ctb", comment = "AI assistant")
    )
Description: Query U.S. Census Bureau data through natural language using large
    language models. Ask questions like "What's the median income in Boston?" or
    "Show me housing data by tract in Framingham, MA" and get answers with
    reproducible tidycensus R code. Powered by ellmer for LLM integration.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Depends: R (>= 4.1)
Encoding: UTF-8
